	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64570361"><p>I'm pretty sure Walmart knows how to use TLS.  Go ahead, sniff all the wifi and bluetooth traffic you like - if the internal protocol uses cryptography in any meaningful way, you just filled a lot of flash cells with pseudo-random trash unless their keys get compromised or use shitty breakable ciphers.</p></div>
	</div>

